      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-28T21:33:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For iOS, we should be using vm_address_t and vm_size_t, because we’ll only ever need to deal with same-bitness.\n\nIn fact, since this is always in-process for us on iOS, this can return a live pointer: const dyld_all_image_infos*.\n\ntask_dyld_info_data_t carries a mach_vm_address_t/mach_vm_size_t pair. This would be the right spot to transform to the type that we’ll be using everywhere else. We expect this to always be a valid transformation because we’re only supporting 64-bit. A checked_cast would be appropriate (and should optimize away).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "fbc3fd552020e02915cb8485c64d3ebe42bb2bd3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
